Re: you know how...?
by Hyperworm » Sun 12.06.2009 11:09 am Another variation is simply "you know ~", as in "You know[=remember] you lent me your camera?"Also, this use of "how" only works in very specific sentence structures and with correct stress.In "Do you know how you lent me your camera?", emphasis on "do", "know", or "how" breaks it and makes "how" into どうやって. Even the presence of "do" almost breaks it by itself. Emphasis on "camera" works though.
