Re: you know how...?
by phreadom » Sun 12.06.2009 1:28 pm I'm not saying it couldn't be used that way. I think it has a lot to do with the tone of how actually say the sentence."You know you lent me your camera.. ? Well... I broke it by accident..." would probably sound fine if the tone matched the other way of saying it.I just wouldn't expect to hear it said that way... I would hear it as a reminder, not a lead in to a further explanation like the other way of saying it. It would make sense once they continued on with the explanation... but initially I would think they were reminding me for the sake of reminding me, not because they wanted to establish that fact before moving on to a further explanation.
